<br>
A guild was having an event in unrest to help a member get a tarnished key from the preist of Najena.  We had some 45+ melees.  After trashing the zone, we left the 30 something group to camp the Priest while we sat down on the first floor.  The ~47th level monk wanted to dual ~45 level warrior.  The necro said he could duel his pet.  He did not want to do that because it would be to wimpy.  But the group called him chicken so he did.  The pet made him give without any problem.  Then the warrior wanted a pieice of the pet.  The warrior did a lot better.  He got the pet down to about 2 bulbs of heath.  Then the paladin wanted to try.  This fight took a lot longer.  The paladin was casting spells, rooting, stuning, healing, and doing quite well.  He got the pet down two bulbs of heath and was at full health when he ran out of mana and went strictly meleely.  When the paladin got to 2 bulbs of heath, the pet was still at 1.5 and the paladin called it quits.  I then challenged the necro with my fully buffed, armor, and focus item fire pet.  He killed the necro's pet with about half his hit points left.  I looked at the logs and noticed that my pet was hitting for max nearly every time.  I suggest we duel again, but let me give the necro pet some armor.  I fully buffed the necro and we dueled again.  The fight was very close with each one getting a slight lead at some point in the battle.  Each pet had about 2 blubs of health left at one point in the batte.  Then, the fire pet moved ahead and won.  After looking at the logs, the necro pet hit more often for larger amounts, but the fireshield and the pets fire attack kept it even.  Then at the tail end of the fight, the necro starting hitting for less {Probably due to damage taken} and it was taking more damage from the fireshield than it was doing in a hit.  Still at the end of the fight, the fire pet had just one bulb of health.  <br>
<br>
So even though our pet cons 41st level, that is mob level and not character level.  Our 41st level pet will most likely defeat a 45 level melee. <br>
<br>
